1. Watt-hour A watt-hour is the energy delivered by one watt of power for one hour. Since one watt is equivalent to one joule per second, a
watt-hour is equivalent to 3600 joules of energy.
Metric prefixes are used for multiples of the unit, usually:
โข kilowatt-hours (kWh), or a thousand watt-hours.
โข Megawatt-hours (MWh), or a million watt-hours.
โข Gigawatt-hours (GWh), or a billion watt-hours.
โข Terawatt-hours (TWh), or a trillion watt-hours.
